I remember being on my last can, just hoping whatever God is out there could spare me yet another drop. The day I could no longer buy WD40 was the day I lost hope. For the 3 months I spent looking for a job, I also spent in a severe state of depression. This depression even led me to lose motivation to find a job. I wanted nothing but to down literally any WD40 i could find. And let me tell you, finding a new job and getting that first paycheck was a moment of pure joy. My flame  reignited as I went to purchase what would be the sweetest, most savory can of WD40 I had ever laid my lips upon. It was empty nearly minutes after I had opened it up to start. I just couldnâ€™t wait for another. I lost all control and spent every last penny from that week of work on WD40. In fact, in the days ahead, I had spent every moment drinking what I could of the liquid. I had a routine, and even rationed my cans  through the days so I couldnâ€™t run out. I pushed through tax evasion, nearly lost my job due to the consumption of oil on the job, and had to deal with house eviction. But I took my time and came out of the miserable spot I was once in. Now I am here, today, enjoying my life to the fullest. As long as I have a can of WD40 in reach, nothing is wrong. Downing WD40>suicide>downloading this garbage app.
